3 Process

3.1 Raw reads

Read the HTSeq files

res <- mclapply(dir("htseq",pattern="*STAR.txt",full.names=TRUE),function(fil){
  read.delim(fil,header=FALSE,stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
},mc.cores=max(mcaffinity()))
names(res) <- gsub("_STAR\\.txt|.*XX_","",dir("htseq",pattern="*STAR.txt"))

Get the count table

addInfo <- c("__no_feature","__ambiguous","__too_low_aQual","__not_aligned","__alignment_not_unique")
sel <- match(addInfo,res[[1]][,1])
count.table <- do.call(cbind,lapply(res,"[",3))[-sel,]
colnames(count.table) <- names(res)
rownames(count.table) <- res[[1]][,1][-sel]
count.table <- count.table[,match(samples$Filename,colnames(count.table))]

write.csv(count.table,file.path(outdir,"raw-unormalised-data.csv"))

3.2 Raw tissues

Compare the raw counts from Phloem and Xylem Keep samples with 10 raw reads in at least 2 replicates In all but 4 cases, we have 4 reps

pander(table(table(paste0(samples$Tissue,samples$Sampling))))
1 2 3
1 3 40

Function

"geneSelect" <- function(tissue,nread=10,nrep=2){
  rowSums(sapply(lapply(
      split.data.frame(t(count.table[,samples$Tissue ==tissue] >= nread),
                       samples[samples$Tissue==tissue,"Sampling"])
    ,colSums), ">=", nrep)) >= 1
}

get the boolean selection by tissue

phloem <- geneSelect("Phloem")
xylem <- geneSelect("Xylem")

Plot the corresponding gene overlap

plot.new()
grid.draw(venn.diagram(list(
  names(phloem)[phloem],
  names(xylem)[xylem]
),
filename=NULL,
col=pal[1:2],
category.names=c("Phloem","Xylem")))

png(file.path(outdir,"phloem_xylem_Venn.png"),width=800,height=800,pointsize = 34)

Extract the gene sets

Phloem.genes <- setdiff(names(phloem)[phloem], names(xylem)[xylem])
write.csv2(Phloem.genes,file.path(outdir,"Phloem.genes"))

Xylem.genes <- setdiff(names(xylem)[xylem],names(phloem)[phloem])

Common.genes <- intersect(names(xylem)[xylem],names(phloem)[phloem])
write.csv2(Common.genes,file.path(outdir,"Common.genes"))

phloem.0.0 <- geneSelect("Phloem",0,1)

load("/mnt/picea/projects/spruce/htuominen/27_SpruceTimeSeries/STAR-unmapped-reads.rda")
all.stats <- rbind.data.frame(count.stats,

3.3.1 Barplots

xnames <- sub("-.*","",samples$Date)
sel <- c(0,which(diff(as.integer(factor(xnames)))!=0))+1
xnames[-sel] <- NA
par(mar=c(6.1,5.1,4.1,2.1))

barplot(as.matrix(count.stats),col=pal[1:3],beside=TRUE,las=2,main="read proportion",
        ylim=range(count.stats) + c(0,2e+7),
        names.arg=xnames)
legend("topright",fill=pal[1:3],legend=
         gsub("_"," ",rownames(count.stats)),
                                  bty="n",cex=0.8)

barplot(as.matrix(all.stats),col=pal[1:4],beside=TRUE,las=2,main="read proportion",
        ylim=range(all.stats) + c(0,2e+7),
        names.arg=xnames)
legend("topright",fill=pal[1:4],legend=
         gsub("_"," ",rownames(all.stats)),
                                  bty="n",cex=0.8)

barplot(t(t(all.stats)/colSums(all.stats))*100,col=pal[1:4],beside=TRUE,las=2,main="read proportion",
        ylim=c(0,100),
        names.arg=xnames)
legend("topleft",fill=pal[1:4],horiz=TRUE,
       legend=gsub("_"," ",rownames(all.stats)),
                                  bty="n",cex=0.8)

par(mar=mar)

3.3.2 Boxplots

boxplot(unlist(count.stats["counted",]/colSums(count.stats)),
        main="counted reads",ylab="percent aligned",ylim=c(0,1))

boxplot(t(all.stats),names=gsub("_"," ",rownames(all.stats)))

3.3.3 Expressed genes

How many genes are not expressed out of a total of 70736 genes?

sel <- rowSums(count.table) == 0
sprintf("%s percent of genes are never expressed",
        round(sum(sel) * 100/ nrow(count.table),digits=1))
## [1] "25.7 percent of genes are never expressed"
sprintf("%s percent of genes are never expressed higher than an expression cutoff of 10 reads in at least 2 replicates",
        round(sum(!(phloem | xylem)) * 100/ nrow(count.table),digits=1))
## [1] "48.9 percent of genes are never expressed higher than an expression cutoff of 10 reads in at least 2 replicates"

3.3.4 More plots

display the per-gene mean expression i.e.Â the mean raw count of every gene across samples is calculated and displayed on a log10 scale

plot(density(log10(rowMeans(count.table))),col=pal[1],
     main="mean raw counts distribution",
     xlab="mean raw counts (log10)")

The same is done for the individual samples colored by sample type

plot.multidensity(log10(count.table),
                  col=pal[as.integer(samples$Tissue)],
                  legend.x="topright",
                  legend = levels(samples$Tissue),
                  legend.col = pal[1:nlevels(samples$Tissue)],
                  main="sample raw counts distribution",
                  xlab="per gene raw counts (log10)")
